A teenager at a school in Finland went on the rampage  shooting dead seven classmates and the headmistress, having first signalled his intentions in a video posted on the Internet.
Finnish Prime Minister Matti Vanhanen described the shooting, the worst in the Nordic country's history, as "a great tragedy."
An 18-year-old student opened fire in a high school in southern Finland  killing eight people including the principal before turning the gun on himself.
"The gunman aimed his weapon at his head and fired,.
Police identified the killer as 18-year-old Pekka-Eric Auvinen, who died from his injuries late after shooting himself
